From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Subject: [PATCH] Fix Stage0 package registration for cross-version bootstrap

When using a newer bootstrap GHC (e.g., 9.6.7 to build 9.2.8), several
issues arise:

1. Boot package dependencies have bootstrap version numbers which don't
   exist in our Stage0 database.

2. Boot package .conf files contain ${pkgroot} which resolves to Stage0's
   lib directory, but library files are in bootstrap's installation.

3. The locally-built RTS has different ABI than bootstrap's base library
   expects, causing undefined symbol errors when linking Stage0 utilities.

This patch makes four key changes:

1. SKIP RTS registration at Stage0. Stage0 utilities (hsc2hs, ghc-pkg, etc.)
   link against bootstrap libraries which expect bootstrap's RTS symbols.
   By not registering our RTS, bootstrap GHC falls back to its global
   package database which has the compatible RTS.

2. Remap dependency versions in copyConf - bootstrap dependencies like
   template-haskell-2.20.0.0 are remapped to source versions like
   template-haskell-2.18.0.0.

3. Use --expand-pkgroot in ghc-pkg describe to convert ${pkgroot} to
   absolute paths pointing to bootstrap's installation.

4. Use 'update' instead of 'register' for idempotent parallel builds.

--- a/hadrian/src/Rules/Register.hs
+++ b/hadrian/src/Rules/Register.hs
